definitions.definition: Food given to (especially herbivorous ) non-human animals.
examples: They sell feed , riding helmets, and everything else for horses.

definitions.definition: The part of a machine that supplies the material to be operated upon.
examples: the paper feed of a printer

definitions.definition: The forward motion of the material fed into a machine.

definitions.label_groups: UK , Australia , New Zealand , colloquial , countable

definitions.definition: A gathering to eat, especially in large quantities.
examples: They held a crab feed on the beach.

subdefinitions.definition: : antichronological sequence of posts or articles from a single source, especially as consumable on a platform other as originally published.
examples: I've subscribed to the feeds of my favourite blogs, so I can find out when new posts are added without having to visit those sites.

subdefinitions.definition: content intended for consumption by scrolling or swiping, especially as a home page and from multiple publishers followed or algorithmically curated
subdefinitions.label_groups: social media , often after a possessive determiner

definitions.definition: A straight man who delivers lines to the comedian during a performance.
